RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 1 5F Dirt CR: 62. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SAVANNAH'S HERE rushed up the rail to be off the pace going into the turn then cut the corner into the stretch and kept on to be up in the final yards. CHACHA TO CATALINA pressed the pace from the two path through the turn then engaged the leader at the top of the stretch to take a brief lead but was run down by the inside closer to be denied. RUN AWAY SAMARI showed no early speed but moved up the rail around the turn and followed the winner in the stretch to be along for the show. GATSBY'S GIFT went to a challenged lead through the turn then fought gamely to mid stretch and tired. TROSKA tracked the leaders on the backstretch then made a mild three wide bid on the turn but lacked a late response. BRIDLED UP trailed the field early then made a four wide bid on the turn to improve position late. BOSTON BELLE was off the pace from between horses to the turn then gave way. APRIORITY GIRL tracked the leaders from two wide to the turn then dropped back.

ENTRY.NAME: Savannah's Here
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, off pace, up final yards

ENTRY.NAME: Run Away Samari
ENTRY.COMMENT: no speed, rail bid, along for show

ENTRY.NAME: Troska
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked leaders, mild bid 3w, lacked late response,

ENTRY.NAME: Chacha to Catalina
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace, brief lead 1/8, ran down

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 2 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 63. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OUR CLOVER GAL vied for the lead from three wide down the backstretch then moved in to the two path to engage the leader after the quarter pole, dueled down the stretch and won the nod. MISS CHARGE IT went to the front to a pressured lead from the inside then dueled to the wire and lost the photo. TERRI GOT A FRIEND settled on the inside to the three furlong marker then moved out to the two path around the final turn, tipped back inside for the stretch run and was up for the show. LEPRECHAUN CHARM stalked the pace from three wide down the backstretch then made a four wide bid on the final turn to improve position in the stretch drive. BELL PEPPER was allowed to settle on the inside down the backstretch then made a three wide bid on the final turn and passed tiring rivals. PINTORA hopped leaving the gate but was rushed up between horse around the first turn and was in contention down the backstretch but tired in the stretch drive. BYE BYE BIG BABY was off the pace while saving ground down the backstretch then retreated on the final turn. MAVE RUNNER pressed the pace from between horses to the three furlong marker and dropped back.

ENTRY.NAME: Terri Got a Friend
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled inside, 2w2nd, rail bid stretch, up show

ENTRY.NAME: Bell Pepper
ENTRY.COMMENT: allowed to settle, 3wturn, passed tiring rivals,

ENTRY.NAME: Pintora
ENTRY.COMMENT: hopped start, rushed up between, tired

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 3 5F Dirt CR: 57. Maiden Claiming Purse 38000. (INCLUDES UP TO $1,400 LTBASBF) FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CUSTOM SUNSHINE sprinted to a clear lead and won going away. BABY JANE was off a step slow then steadily advanced through the turn and made a late rally. COAL DANCER chased the leaders but was no match for the winner. BACK STREET BABY was void of the early speed, made a bid into the turn but had to steady in the traffic but made a rebid in the stretch to improve her position. EVE EVE trailed the field and passed tired rivals. RT'S MYSTERY LADY saved ground to no avail. FIVE LEAF CLOVER was off slow then rushed to contention to press the early pace but lost action into the turn and was done.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 4 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 66. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: VIEWING TRAIL saved ground throughout, made an inside bid on the turn and slipped through at the eighth pole and drew clear. ACELA EXPRESS stalked the pace from three wide through the final turn and made a late run but was no match for the inside rival. OLD SCHOOL FLASH vied for the lead from between horses to the three furlong marker then moved to engage the leader at the quarter pole, matched strides to the sixteenth pole but was outfinished by the inside and outside closers. PIECE OF ME shot away from the gate to take a clear lead around the first turn then set the pace through the final turn and was challenged in the stretch drive and tired. BROOKE'S ALL IN raced in the middle of the pace from two or three wide but didn't make a bid. ABSOLUTELY MINDY was allowed to settle near the back and was never a factor. THAT YOU MARGARET trailed the field and was outrun. CALIFORNIA CALI went five wide into the first turn then was allowed to settle down the backstretch but was never a threat.

ENTRY.NAME: Viewing Trail
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, inside bid turn, slip thru, drew clear,

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 5 5F Dirt CR: 81. Claiming Purse 11000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023. RACE.FOOTNOTES: LA TRESS GRAY raced in the middle of the pack on the inside down the backstretch, made a two wide bid on the turn to engage the leader and drew off in the stretch. ITSNOTMYJOB went to a clear early lead on the backstretch then was engaged on the turn but couldn't fend off the outside rival but proved second best. HOLY WAR chased the leader to the turn then moved up and went three wide into the stretch for a late run to be up for the third place money. KNIGHTS SWORD raced off the pace from three wide to the turn then tipped in to the rail on the turn but was empty in the stretch. POINT OF VICTORY showed no early speed then moved up going three wide at the three sixteenths pole but lacked the late kick needed. IRON LOTUS tracked the leaders from two wide to the quarter pole and retreated. ESSENTIAL BELLA rushed up from four wide to be in contention around the turn but tired in the stretch.

ENTRY.COMMENT: middle of pack, 2wturn, engaged, drew off,

RACE.FOOTNOTES: THAT IS AWESOME roused to the front to a clear lead from the first half then was pressured through the final turn but came again to draw clear. MOR KISSES prompted the pace for the first half then vied for the lead from two wide through the final turn but couldn't over take the leader and was a clear second. COUSIN VICKIE raced in the middle of the pack from the inside down the backstretch then made a rail bid on the final turn and kept on for the show. PAYTON'S INDIAN raced off the pace from three wide to the top of the stretch and tired. EASY ACT was allowed to settle near the back and passed tiring rivals. CAT B CAUSE raced in the middle of the pack from off the rail to the final turn and faded. AUNT JANA was always back. RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 7 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 96. Allowance Purse 36000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, WAIVER CLAIMING, STARTER OR TRIAL OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since November 18 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since October 18 Allowed 4 lbs. (Claiming Races Not Considered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DONEGAL FACTOR broke outward then swerved back in but went five wide into the first turn, was rushed up to be off the pace on the backstretch from three wide and moved up to make a bid going into the stretch and was up in the final jumps. CLASSIC BET pressed the pace from the inside then over took the leader at the three sixteenths pole but dueled with an outside closer and gave way grudgingly. JOLLY TOMMY moved between horse at the half mile marker to track the leaders through the final turn then moved out to three wide in upper stretch for the late run but was too late. UPTOWN SOCIAL roused to a pressured lead to the three sixteenths and gave way. MAYFIELD STRONG raced in the middle of the pack while saving ground, made a mild bid on the final turn and finished evenly. GOD'S GOLD was unhurried down the backstretch then made a three wide bid on the final turn to improve position. MR MIDWAY raced in the middle of the pack while saving ground and dropped back on the backstretch. EL ORO (FR) was forced in and bumped with JOLLY TOMMY on the first turn and had to steady, settled slightly leaving the turn then rushed to contention down the backstretch from four wide and tired on the final turn.
